.TH pop 4
.SH NAME
.PP
\*Lpop\*O \- POP database of subscribers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.sS
\*L/usr/spool/pop/POP\*O
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "POP database"
.iX "pop"
The POP database contains the following entry for each POP subscriber:
.oS
\*Vname\*L::\*Vprimary_file\*L:\*Vencrypted_passwd\*L:: \*Vuser\*L@<\*Vclient_address\*L>::::0\*O
.oE
.PP
The fields represent the following:
.VL 4m
.LI "\*Vname\*O"
The POP subsriber's username
.LI "\*Vprimary_file\*O"
The mail drop for the POP subscriber (relative to the POP directory)
.LI "\*Vencrypted_passwd\*O"
The POP subscriber's password generated by \*Lpopwrd\*O(8)
.LI "\*Vuser\*L@<\*Vclient_address\*L>"
The remote user allowed to make remote POP (RPOP) connections
.LE
.PP
This database is an ASCII file.  Each field within each POP subscriber's
entry is separated from the next by a colon.  Each POP subscriber
is separated from the next by a new-line.  If the password field is
null, then no password is valid.
.PP
To add a new POP subscriber, edit the file adding a line such as the
following:
.oS
\*Lmrose::mrose:::::::0i\*O
.oE
.PP
Then, use popwrd to set the password for the  POP  subscriber.  If
you wish to allow POP subscribers to access their maildrops without
supplying a password (by using privileged ports), fill-in the network
address field, as in:
.oS
\*Lmrose::mrose:::mrose@nrtc-isc::::0\*O
.oE
.PP
which permits "mrose@nrtc-isc" to access the maildrop for  the  POP
subscriber "mrose".  Multiple network addresses may be specified by
separating them with commas, as in:
.br
.oS
\*Ldave::dave:9X5/m4yWHvhCc::dave@romano.wisc.edu,dave@rsch.wisc.edu::::\*O
.oE
.PP
To disable a POP subscriber from receiving mail, set the primary
file name to the empty string.  To prevent a  POP  subscriber  from
picking-up mail, set the encrypted password to "*" and set the
network address to the empty string.
.PP
This file resides in home directory of the login "pop."  Because of
the encrypted passwords, it can and does have general read permission.
.SH FILES
.PP
.VL 11m
.LI "\*L/usr/spool/pop/POP\*O"
POP database.
.LE
.SH RELATED INFORMATION
.PP
Commands: \*Lspop\*O(1), \*Lpopaka\*O(8), \*Lpopd\*O(8), \*Lpopwrd\*O(8).
